{"title":"What It Takes to Beat the Kokopelli Trail FKT with Peter Stetina","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/23/stetina-kokopelli-trail-fkt/","date":1627047732000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span>Sure, we all would love to spend more than 10 hours straight hammering the pedals across 140 agonizing miles to snag the fastest known time on one of off-road endurance cycling’s most coveted routes. What’s not to like?</span></p><p><span>Lucky for those of us who can’t, or feel queasy at the very thought, pro cyclist <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/03/23/how-long-can-we-keep-up-with-gravel-racing-pro-peter-stetina/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Peter Stetina</a> brought along cameras for his latest FKT attempt on the Kokopelli Trail. The trail cuts through a healthy mix of dirt, gravel, single track, and Jeep roads spanning the distance from Loma, Colorado to Moab, Utah.</span></p><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"YouTube video player\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/bTxqssKKivc\" width=\"1019\" height=\"573\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" ezoid=\"0.16792804009513795\"></iframe></p><p><span>Spoiler alert: he snagged the top time at 10:24:43. But like the ride itself, Canyon Bicycles’ 25-minute feature covering Stetina’s ride, which premiered on July 22, is more about the journey than the destination.</span></p><p><span>And the journey is a bit of a doozy.</span></p><figure id=\"attachment_266307\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-266307\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main.jpg\" alt=\"Peter Stetina in new Kokopelli doc\" width=\"2500\" height=\"1667\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main.jpg 2500w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-2048x1366.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-1920x1280.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb26 src ng ngcb26 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main.jpg 2500w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-1536x1024.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-2048x1366.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-1920x1280.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/22233248/kokopelli-main-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-266307\">all images c. Canyon</figcaption></figure><h2>Ultra-Enduring the Kokopelli Trail</h2><p><span>Ultra-endurance cyclists are a different breed. These men and women revel in the challenge of riding absurd distances in unfathomable times to claim a spot, sometimes only briefly, in trail history.</span></p><p><span>In a sport that often shirks at the idea of any kind of support — even in the form of a boost in motivation from a film crew or loved ones cheering you on — inside looks at the grueling nature of some of the longest, toughest rides in the world are a relative rarity.</span></p><p><span>I’d love to say Stetina makes the ride look like a delightful trollop through the wilderness. But Canyon’s film crew perfectly captured why the upper echelon of extreme endurance cycling is such a niche community.</span></p><p><a hr